**Topic** : AI Context window

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Article Source** :

- **[What is a context window in AI? Understanding its importance in LLMs](https://nebius.com/blog/posts/context-window-in-ai)**
- Research Paper : **[Exploring Context Window of Large Language Models](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2405.18009)**

**TL;DR** :

In the context of AI, particularly with Large Language Models (LLMs), a context window refers to the amount of text (measured in tokens) that an LLM can process and consider at any given time. Chunking is a technique used to break down large documents or pieces of text into smaller, manageable segments (chunks) to fit within the LLM's context window. This is essential because LLMs have limitations on how much text they can handle in a single input.
